<h3>Significance</h3>
<ol>
<li>1 bn directly depend on wetland</li>
<li><strong>40% </strong>diversity on <em><strong>6%</strong></em> wetland area.</li>
<li>1/3 land based carbon stored in wetlands&nbsp;</li>
<li>coastline erosion + floods +&nbsp;</li></ol>
<h3>Threats&nbsp;</h3>
<ol>
<li>as per <span style="color:#8e44ad">IPBES</span>,&nbsp; disappearing 3x than forests.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li></ol>
<table border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:500px">
<tbody>
<tr>
	<td>soil</td>
	<td>&nbsp;land degradation + salination&nbsp;</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td>water</td>
	<td>&nbsp;pollution + eutrophication + excessive extraction of water + high T and evaporation</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td>vegetation</td>
	<td>deforestation + invasive species like water hyacinth (east kolkata wetlands)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td>size of wetland</td>
	<td>urbanisation&nbsp; + encroachment</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
<p>India = 4.5% wetland area and 42 ramsar sites.</p>
<p>MEASURES&nbsp;</p>
<ol>
<li>national wetland conservation programme</li>
<li><strong>National Centre for Sustainable Coastal Management =&nbsp;mapped the Hazard Line for the entire coast of India,</strong>&nbsp;which includes vulnerability mapping of flood, erosion and sea-level rise.</li></ol>
